RIYADH: King Salman received on Sunday a written message from President Sadyr Japarov of the Republic of Kyrgyzstan, regarding relations between the two countries and peoples, and ways to strengthen them in various fields and at all levels, Saudi Press Agency (SPA) reported. The message was received by Prince Faisal bin Farhan, Minister of Foreign Affairs, during his meeting in Riyadh with Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Kyrgyzstan Zheenbek Kulubaev Moldokanovich. During the meeting, they also reviewed ways to enhance cooperation between the two countries and opportunities to develop them. The two sides also discussed a number of regional and international issues and latest developments of common interest. The meeting was attended by Undersecretary of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs for Political Affairs Ambassador Dr. Saud Al-Sati, and Kyrgyz Ambassador to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia Ulukbek Maripov.